Second: Stack Cleanup: While the standard Windows x64 Calling Convention typically requires the caller to clean up the stack, ret n can be used to pop an additional n bytes from the stack upon returning ( the stack will increase in size when sub, decrease in size when add more space to it) so in this.
ret n mean Pops the return address to rip AND then adds n to RSP

